LDK Solar Co., a Chinese maker of
solar energy products, raised $164.2 million from a follow-on
public offering of 13.8 million American Depositary Shares, the
company said in a statement.  The sale included 1.8 million shares for the underwritersâ€™
over-allotment option, which was taken up in full, LDK Solar
said.  Each ADS represents one ordinary share in the company. The
underwriters were Citigroup Global Markets Inc., Deutsche Bank
Securities Inc. and  UBS AG .  To contact the reporter on this story:
